    • Class com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message.OutMessage extends Message implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • resourcePath

          Resource resourcePath
          the Resource path where the REST request needs to be sent to

        • statusCode

          int statusCode
          the status code sent back by the server in the response to this OutMessage

        • state

          OutMessageState state
          the OutMessageState that this OutMessage instance is currently in

        • bigData

          boolean bigData
          property indicating whether this OutMessage instance represents a big data or no. e.g. An out message that sends image to the server is bigData.

        • callback

          SimplyReliableMsgIntf callback
          Deprecated. consider using OutMessage.baseCallback
          the callback on which the methods will be called after getting the appropriate response from the server

        • baseCallback

          BaseCallback baseCallback
          the callback on which the methods will be called after getting the appropriate response from the server

        • rawResponse

          String rawResponse
          the raw string representation of the response returned by the server

        • rawResponseContentType

          String rawResponseContentType
          the content type of the raw response that is received from the server

        • async

          boolean async
          a boolean value indicating whether this OutMessage instance is an async message or no. Async messages are stored in the persistence store and outlive even app resets. Sync messages are the exact opposite of their async counterparts

        • updateMsgComponentsIntf

          UpdateMsgComponentsIntf updateMsgComponentsIntf
          the callback that will run whenever all the dependencies associated with this OutMessage instance are fulfilled. This callback will usually update the Message components like url and body before sending it out to the server

        • msgComponentsInitializedMap

          HashMap<K,V> msgComponentsInitializedMap
          a map that will store the mapping between the msg component name and whether it is initialized or no

        • locationRedirection

          String locationRedirection
          the location where the redirection should happen. Can be null if there was no redirection response for this OutMessage instance

        • tagsMap

          HashMap<K,V> tagsMap
          This will contain the mapping of the tag status to the message. The tag status corresponds to the state of this OutMessage and is one of the constants OutMessage.TAG_BEING_SENT, OutMessage.TAG_SUCCESS or OutMessage.TAG_FAILURE

        • rootUrl

          String rootUrl
          message specific root url

    • Class com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message.resthttp.GetMessage extends OutMessage implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • responseType

          Type responseType
          A response type instance representing the entire response structure that is expected out of this get request. This responseType will be used by the internal Gson facility to do the unmarshalling of response json data

          e.g. Type fooType = new TypeToken<Foo<Bar>>() {}.getType();

        • file

          File file
          the file that will store the success response for this get message. This is so that immediately after reading the response from the input stream, if the phone gets switched off or the battery goes low, the message processing can resume by reading the response stored in this file.

        • queryParams

          QueryParams queryParams
          the QueryParams that need to be appended to a GET REST request to be sent to the server

    • Class com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message.resthttp.MultiPartGetMessage extends GetMessage implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • fullFilePath

          String fullFilePath
          the entire file path (till the name of the file) where the byte data of the response will be saved. This is useful for cases where for a GetMessage call we expect application/octet-stream data from the server. Basically for cases where image/video/pdf document/any other type needs to be downloaded from the server

        • multiPartFile

          File multiPartFile
          represents the multipart file that is downloaded from the server and stored in the File instance

        • contentLength

          long contentLength
          the length in bytes, of the content that needs to be downloaded from the server

        • acceptByteRanges

          boolean acceptByteRanges
          whether for the download, the server side implementation accepts byte ranges

        • lastBytesDownloaded

          long lastBytesDownloaded
          the no of bytes that was downloaded till the last time. Useful for resume

        • downloadInfoRetrieved

          boolean downloadInfoRetrieved
          a boolean value indicating whether the information regarding this download, has been retrieved or no. Whether the Head call for this download is completed or no
